Study

Default: all pods can talk to all pods. NetworkPolicy = whitelist.
Requires a CNI that supports it (Calico, Cilium; flannel does not).
Ingress and egress rules; podSelector, namespaceSelector, ipBlock.
Hands-On

# Deny all ingress in namespace
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata: {name: deny-all, namespace: dev}
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes: [Ingress]
---
# Allow only from app=frontend
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata: {name: allow-frontend}
spec:
  podSelector: {matchLabels: {app: backend}}
  ingress:
  - from:
    - podSelector: {matchLabels: {app: frontend}}

Test with kubectl exec ... -- wget -qO- backend.
